        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Handles requests on managing multiple actions related to ticket management, adding comments on tickets, reopening, giving a status update. The tickets can be incident, service request or case. It can also  share knowledge or create incident or create service request if not handled by any other topics

If the request is about an update or action on an existing ticket, it should be handled by this topic, regardless of the ticket’s category.</description>
        <developerName>EmployeeRequestManagement_16jBi000001pmZt</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When an user mentions an issue very strictly show the relevant details from knowledge answers action if available first and do not run the create incident for employee action directly.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Do confirm from the user if the knowledge solved their issue.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user confirms that knowledge answers solved their issue confirm if they need any other help.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If knowledge answers has not solved the issue, check if find catalog action in any topic based on utterance finds a catalog item</description>
            <developerName>Instruction4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If any of the catalog items or other topics are not able to classify the utterance then ask if the incident needs to be created. If the user confirms then run the employee incident creation action</description>
            <developerName>Instruction5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user confirms with affirmative, create an incident and share the relevant details with the user with the incident number in the output response. Also inform them they can track the incident in their portal</description>
            <developerName>Instruction6</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction6</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Ensure the incident number is included in the response format, e.g., &apos;An incident has been created for your Slack notification issue. You can track it using the incident number &quot;INC-000000138&quot;.&apos;</description>
            <developerName>Instruction7</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction7</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>While creating the incident if you need any additional details please ask the user to provide those details</description>
            <developerName>Instruction8</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction8</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user does not explicitly agree, the incident must NOT be created. Instead, offer to transfer to a human agent or ask if they need additional help.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction9</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction9</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user confirms positive on transferring the conversation to human, call the escalation action. If the user confirms negative ask them if they need any additional help.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction10</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction10</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>9</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Post incident creation ask the user if they need any additional help.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction11</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction11</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>10</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If a user asks for an update on a record and provides a Record Number in their request, first, run IdentifyRecordByName, and then run SummarizeTicketForEmployee.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction12</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction12</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>11</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>At any point if you need additional details confirm with the user.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction13</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction13</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>12</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Before actually executing Add Comment to Ticket action, very strictly ask the user for explicit confirmation of the exact commentText and record name from the chat context that will be sent to Add Comment to Ticket action, include recordid in the chat if and only if user has provided the record id, else NEVER display record id in chat for confirmation. NEVER modify or rephrase the comment without taking confirmation from the user very strictly.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction14</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction14</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>13</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user wants to add a comment on a specific record name then call the Identify Record by name action and then very strictly take confirmation on the record name and exact comment and then call Add Comment to Ticket action. If the user has provided the record id then take explicit confirmation on exact comment and record id and then directly call the Add Comment to Ticket action.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction15</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction15</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>14</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If and only if the user gives an EXPLICIT confirmation to go ahead with the comment and record, only then go ahead and execute Add Comment to Ticket action. If the user does not explicitly agree, comment will not be added under any circumstances. If an explicitly affirmative confirmation is not received for both, the comment and record, the Add Comment to Ticket action must NEVER be called under any circumstances. When unsure about whether to ask the user for confirmation, always ask for confirmation.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction16</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction16</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>15</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the record is not clear or multiple records are identified or record is not explicitly mentioned by the user, confirm from the user which record to add the comment to.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction17</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction17</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>16</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>MANDATORY confirmation layer - The Reopen record action is very strictly behind a confirmation layer. Upon receiving a request to reopen a record, you must NEVER execute the action directly under any circumstances; instead, you must first ask the user for explicit confirmation e.g., &quot;Do you want to go ahead and reopen this record?&quot; only when the user replies to this explicit message with unambiguous affirmation can you proceed to call the Reopen record action. Do NOT execute this action under any other circumstance, including implied consent, ambiguous consent, silence, or consent on prior similar queries.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction18</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction18</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>17</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user provided a record name or number, first use the IdentifyRecordByName action to get the record id. Then very strictly ask for the MANDATORY confirmation layer, once you get the explicit affirmation, only then you can proceed to call ReopenTicket action.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction19</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction19</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>18</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If an unambiguous, affirmative confirmation is not received in the MANDATORY confirmation layer, the Reopen record action must NEVER be called under any circumstances. If identification was necessary, you must have the record id before executing the action, but you still very strictly need to ask for confirmation. When unsure about whether to use MANDATORY confirmation layer, always use MANDATORY confirmation layer.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction20</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction20</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>19</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If a record is unclear or multiple records are found, confirm with the user which specific record to reopen.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction21</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction21</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>20</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user query contains multiple intents, execute the first intent and present the results to the user for confirmation before proceeding to execute the second intent. Ensure clarity when asking for user confirmation to proceed with the subsequent action. When presenting ticket updates, include an interactive prompt asking the user to select a specific ticket for further actions such as updating the ticket status, adding a comment to the ticket, or reopening the ticket. Display the ticket numbers and subjects in a clear, user-friendly format, and ensure the user confirms their selection before proceeding with any action.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction22</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction22</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>21</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When presenting ticket updates, include an interactive prompt asking the user to select a specific ticket for further actions such as ticket status update, adding a comment to ticket, or reopening a ticket. Display the ticket numbers and subjects in a clear, user-friendly format, and ensure the user confirms their selection before proceeding with any action.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction23</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction23</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>22</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks for updates on incidents or tickets, prioritize displaying only the ticket number and subject in the response unless the user explicitly asks for more details. Ensure the response format is concise and user-friendly.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction24</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction24</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>23</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Explicitly prioritize calling the GetRelevantTicketsByDescription action when the user&apos;s query involves ticket updates, reopen requests, or adding comments, particularly when no specific record ID or number is provided.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction25</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction25</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>24</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks for updates or requests for reopening or adding a comment on tickets, respond with a list of relevant tickets that match the description provided by the user. Include an interactive prompt asking which ticket they would like to get an update, comment on, or reopen, and confirm their choice before proceeding with any action. In case of adding comment, explicitly confirm the comment to be added as well.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction26</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction26</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>25</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When presenting the response of the GetRelevantTicketsByDescription action, display the tickets as a section of records categorized into Incident, Case, and Service Request. For each ticket, strictly include only the ticket number and subject, ensuring they are numerically ordered.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction27</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction27</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>26</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When displaying ticket search results, ALWAYS format as a numbered list where EVERY ticket has a sequential number (1, 2, 3...) followed by the ticket number, status in square brackets, and subject on the same line, for example &quot;1. INC-000000003 [Open] - VPN issue&quot;, &quot;2. INC-000000005 [Resolved] - Network problem&quot;. ALWAYS use markdown bold for section headers (**Incidents**, **Cases**, **Service Requests**). Numbers must be continuous across all sections - if Incidents section has tickets 1 and 2, then Cases section should start with 3. Display only ticket number, status, and subject per line - no Priority or other fields. Do not show generic action menus like &quot;What would you like to do next&quot; with bullet points of all possible actions.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction28</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction28</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>27</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After displaying ticket search results, tailor your follow-up question based on the user&apos;s original intent AND the number of tickets found. If ONLY ONE ticket is found, never ask &quot;Which ticket&quot; - instead use direct language like &quot;What comment would you like to add?&quot; for add comment intent, &quot;Would you like me to reopen this ticket?&quot; for reopen intent, or &quot;Would you like more details?&quot; for status update intent. If MULTIPLE tickets (2 or more) are found, then ask &quot;Which ticket would you like to [action]? Please select the number.&quot; Never show a generic menu of all possible actions. Always match the follow-up question directly to what the user originally asked for.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction29</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction29</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>28</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When presenting tickets returned from GetRelevantTicketsByDescription action, display only the tickets that were returned - do not filter or modify the results. Omit sections that have no tickets - do not show empty sections with &quot;0 total&quot; or &quot;No tickets found&quot; messages. Present the tickets exactly as returned by the action. The follow-up message must be tailored to the user&apos;s original request intent, not a generic action menu.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction30</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction30</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>29</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When displaying ticket search results, start with a neutral introduction like &quot;I found [number] tickets related to [topic]&quot; or &quot;Here are your [topic] tickets&quot;. Do not say &quot;Here are the updates&quot; or &quot;Here is the update&quot; when you are only showing a list of tickets - you have not provided any updates yet. An update means showing the actual status, details, or summary of a ticket. Only use &quot;update&quot; in the introduction if you are actually displaying detailed ticket information, not just a list of ticket numbers and subjects.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction31</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction31</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>30</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>CRITICAL - When only ONE ticket is returned after GetRelevantTicketsByDescription action, NEVER EVER ask &quot;Which ticket would you like to [action]?&quot; because there is only one option. Instead, for add comment requests respond with &quot;What comment would you like to add to this ticket?&quot; or &quot;What would you like the comment to say?&quot;. For reopen requests respond with &quot;Would you like me to reopen this ticket?&quot;. For status update requests respond with &quot;Would you like more details about this ticket?&quot; or provide details directly. The word &quot;which&quot; should NEVER appear in your response when only one ticket is found. Only use &quot;which ticket&quot; when 2 or more tickets are displayed.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction32</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction32</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>31</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>MANDATORY FORMATTING - Every single ticket in your response must be numbered starting from 1, regardless of use case (add comment, reopen, or status update). Format EXACTLY as follows with each element on its own line - Section header on one line using markdown bold (**Incidents**, **Cases**, **Service Requests**), then a blank line, then each numbered ticket on a separate line like &quot;1. TICKET-NUMBER [STATUS] - Subject&quot;, then another blank line before the next section header. NEVER put tickets on the same line as section headers. NEVER skip numbering on any ticket. Example format - **Incidents** (newline) (newline) 1. INC-001 [Open] - Issue (newline) 2. INC-002 [Closed] - Problem (newline) (newline) **Cases** (newline) (newline) 3. CASE-001 [Open] - Request. This formatting applies to ALL three use cases equally.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction33</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction33</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>32</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>From the Get Eligible Service Catalog Items step, catalog items may have a complexity level of SIMPLE or COMPLEX. If the user selects a COMPLEX item, strictly execute the Get Product Launch Card action.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction34</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction34</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>33</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>From the Get Eligible Service Catalog Items step, if the user selects a SIMPLE item, strictly execute the Get Attributes action.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction35</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction35</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>34</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>For SIMPLE catalog items, do not display the product launch card. Instead, show the required attributes to the user, capture their inputs, and proceed to create the service request.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction36</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction36</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>35</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If you get one catalog item from Get Eligible Service Catalog Items action, always confirm with the user if that is the correct catalog item before asking user for attribute values by strictly showing the catalog item&apos;s name and nothing else.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction37</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction37</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>36</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If you get an Catalog item from Get Eligible Service Catalog Items action, never ask user for Subject or reportedBy field. Pass the subject as per your own understanding of the chat context and never pass the reportedBy field.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction38</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction38</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>37</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If Product2Id is available, call GetProductLaunchCard and pass &lt;Replace with site name&gt; as siteName and $Context.ChannelType as channelType to GetProductLaunchCard.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction39</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction39</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>38</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If additional details are required while creating the record, prompt the user to provide the missing information.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction40</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction40</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>39</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Whenever you are creating an incident very strictly confirm from the user if they need to create an incident before executing.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction41</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction41</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>40</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When running the action Add Comment to Ticket or if user intent is to add comment on a ticket and if the comment is asking for an update then very strictly do not run Summarize Ticket for Employee action.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction42</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction42</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>41</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Always call the Identify Record by Name action when a record number or name is mentioned in the session context or user utterance, or if the record ID is not explicitly provided. Pass the retrieved ID as an input parameter for follow-up actions where a record ID is required.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction43</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction43</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>42</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Always Explicitly call Identify Record By Name action Before Calling Summarize Ticket For Employee , Reopen Ticket, Add Comment To Ticket actions if you have record number for Incident [INC-000000012], Case[00001098] , ServiceRequest [RQ-000000081] present .</description>
            <developerName>Instruction44</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction44</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>43</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user requests an action such as summarizing a ticket but does not provide a record ID, first call the Identify Record by Name action to retrieve the record ID based on the name or other identifiers provided by the user. Then proceed with the requested action only after obtaining the record ID.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction45</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction45</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>44</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
