Cloud Resource Management: &apos;Request New Cloud Service&apos; (e.g., &apos;New AWS S3 Bucket,&apos; &apos;Request Azure SQL Database&apos;), &apos;Modify Cloud Resource&apos; (e.g., &apos;Change IAM policy,&apos; &apos;Adjust security group rules&apos;), &apos;Request Cloud Cost Report.&apos;

Server &amp; Virtual Machine (VM) Management: &apos;Request New Server/VM,&apos; &apos;Reboot Server,&apos; &apos;Report Server Down,&apos; &apos;Request Server Decommission,&apos; &apos;Modify Server Resources&apos; (e.g., &apos;Increase RAM/CPU,&apos; &apos;Expand disk space&apos;).

Platform &amp; Data Services: &apos;Report Database Performance Issue,&apos; &apos;Request Database Backup/Restore,&apos; &apos;Report Kubernetes (K8s) Cluster Issue,&apos; &apos;Request New Database User,&apos; &apos;Troubleshoot CI/CD Pipeline Failure.&apos;

Infrastructure Monitoring &amp; Alerts: &apos;Report High Server CPU,&apos; &apos;Alert for Low Disk Space,&apos; &apos;Investigate Platform Latency,&apos; &apos;Request New Monitoring Alert.</scope>
